01:03:47,480 --> 01:03:48,913
A lot of people say that to me.

919
01:03:49,000 --> 01:03:52,788
He's so quiet and speaks
dead nice to you, using his manners.

920
01:03:52,880 --> 01:03:54,836
You don't see many round here using 'em.

921
01:03:54,920 --> 01:03:57,036
He's a bastard, really.

922
01:03:57,120 --> 01:04:00,271
He likes for people to think
that he's nice, and a lot do,

923
01:04:01,120 --> 01:04:04,476
but I'd love those people
to come round to ours when he starts.

924
01:04:04,560 --> 01:04:07,552
- Has he done it to you before?
- It's his favourite thing.

925
01:04:07,640 --> 01:04:09,312
He's always done it.

926
01:04:09,400 --> 01:04:12,915
What gets me is he doesn't stop
until I'm out cold on the floor.

927
01:04:13,000 --> 01:04:14,558
He's a bastard.

928
01:04:14,640 --> 01:04:16,676
I think I'm gonna have to leave him.

929
01:04:16,760 --> 01:04:19,718
- When?
- As soon as possible.

930
01:04:19,800 --> 01:04:22,758
- He's terrible. He's going nuts.
- What do you mean?

931
01:04:22,840 --> 01:04:25,638
He's hitting me that much,
I can't stand it any more.

932
01:04:25,720 --> 01:04:27,199
I feel I've got to get out.

933
01:04:27,280 --> 01:04:30,875
- I've got to get away from him.
- What, for good or just for a while?

934
01:04:30,960 --> 01:04:33,918
For good for me, and this baby.

935
01:04:34,000 --> 01:04:37,276
I've got to get away for good.

936
01:04:37,360 --> 01:04:41,069
I mean, if he's hitting me really bad
now, what's he going to do to the baby?

937
01:04:41,160 --> 01:04:44,118
- He wouldn't harm a baby.
- Oh, but he would.

938
01:04:44,200 --> 01:04:47,351
I won't give him the chance
to lay his hands on that.

939
01:04:47,440 --> 01:04:51,558
If he can do it to me while I'm pregnant
he can do it to the baby once it's born.

940
01:05:02,400 --> 01:05:05,836
2002, I went to jail.

941
01:05:05,920 --> 01:05:11,631
I was at the scene
of a guy robbing a woman.

942
01:05:11,720 --> 01:05:14,518
The police knew I hadn't
actually committed the robbery

943
01:05:14,600 --> 01:05:17,876
and all they wanted was his name
but I was too scared to give his name

944
01:05:17,960 --> 01:05:20,872
so I ended up pleading guilty
to the robbery

945
01:05:20,960 --> 01:05:23,520
and getting two years, seven months.

946
01:05:30,240 --> 01:05:34,438
In fact I can honestly say, the best
time of my life were that sentence,

947
01:05:34,520 --> 01:05:36,033
where it was easy.

948
01:05:37,920 --> 01:05:41,390
It's just nice, no worries,
no freedom, no abuse.

949
01:05:41,480 --> 01:05:44,711
Erm, being cared for.

950
01:05:44,800 --> 01:05:48,918
Because freedom had give me
nothing but headache and trouble.

951
01:05:52,520 --> 01:05:57,674
I was still using heroin throughout
that sentence. I was getting it sent in.

952
01:05:57,760 --> 01:06:00,149
It's not hard to get drugs in prison.

953
01:06:09,840 --> 01:06:12,832
Act 2, Scene 9.

954
01:06:12,920 --> 01:06:16,071
This is a scene of the girl
and Maureen in the refuge.

955
01:06:17,440 --> 01:06:19,590
I'll be glad when I've had this baby.

956
01:06:19,680 --> 01:06:21,955
What you gonna call it?

957
01:06:22,040 --> 01:06:26,033
Julie, if it's a girl, or Lorraine.

958
01:06:26,120 --> 01:06:28,793
And Jason or Christopher
if it's a lad.

959
01:06:29,800 --> 01:06:31,631
I'm glad we got away from that dump.

960
01:06:32,800 --> 01:06:37,157
It may be a dump, but I quite miss it.

961
01:06:37,240 --> 01:06:38,389
I miss my mum

962
01:06:39,520 --> 01:06:41,829
and all the kids

963
01:06:41,920 --> 01:06:46,391
and funnily enough,
I quite miss me dad and all me mates.

964
01:06:46,480 --> 01:06:49,916
And it's a bit quiet here, innit?

965
01:07:03,560 --> 01:07:07,473
Within 30 days of getting out of prison,
I was pregnant with Harris.

966
01:07:10,480 --> 01:07:13,313
Cos I let her stay here
when she got out of prison.

967
01:07:13,400 --> 01:07:17,518
She'd just found out she were pregnant
with Harris after she'd been here.

968
01:07:17,600 --> 01:07:20,160
And she didn't take a suitcase with her

969
01:07:20,240 --> 01:07:23,232
and she'd left some clean clothes
on the side.

970
01:07:23,320 --> 01:07:25,914
So I went to put 'em in a suitcase.
I weren't looking.

971
01:07:26,000 --> 01:07:29,709
I seen a chemist bag with one of
my kitchen spoons hanging out of it.

972
01:07:29,800 --> 01:07:31,518
So I thought, "What's this?"

973
01:07:31,600 --> 01:07:34,114
A dirty great big needle
hanging out of that bag

974
01:07:34,200 --> 01:07:36,236
and there was still heroin on the spoon.

975
01:07:36,320 --> 01:07:40,074
So obviously I went mad. I wrapped it up
in a tea towel, put it in the bag

976
01:07:40,160 --> 01:07:43,357
and I went all the way to Bradford
because I were gonna kill her.

977
01:07:43,440 --> 01:07:46,910
Cos my little one could have picked
that up, do you know what I mean?

978
01:07:47,000 --> 01:07:49,753
And I were really mad with her.

979
01:07:49,840 --> 01:07:52,434
But then I found out
she'd cut her tag off as well.

980
01:07:52,520 --> 01:07:54,476
I didn't know that she'd had a tag.

981
01:07:54,560 --> 01:07:57,472
She'd cut it off
before she come to my house.

982
01:08:00,920 --> 01:08:02,990
The birth, Ann was there.

983
01:08:04,400 --> 01:08:06,311
She was the first to hold him.

984
01:08:06,400 --> 01:08:09,517
And I actually cried when I had Harris.

985
01:08:09,600 --> 01:08:13,149
He was the first baby
that I really, really wanted.

986
01:08:16,080 --> 01:08:17,991
I stayed mostly clean.

987
01:08:18,080 --> 01:08:23,313
I used maybe once every two week
through Harris's pregnancy.

988
01:08:23,400 --> 01:08:26,233
He was born an addict. Erm...

989
01:08:28,000 --> 01:08:30,309
He was my everything.

990
01:08:33,480 --> 01:08:35,948
I bet Rafee's about 50 now.

991
01:08:36,880 --> 01:08:38,791
I made him hold Harris.

992
01:08:38,880 --> 01:08:42,793
And he was so pleased with himself
cos he'd never held a baby before.

993
01:08:42,880 --> 01:08:46,634
And he used to make sure Harris had
everything, make sure I had everything.

994
01:08:46,720 --> 01:08:50,998
Cigarettes, food in the cupboard,
blah-di blah-di blah...

995
01:08:51,080 --> 01:08:53,799
In the back of my head
he was a client, but he wasn't,

996
01:08:53,880 --> 01:08:58,237
if you know what I mean.
It was different, you know.

997
01:08:58,320 --> 01:09:02,233
He was a sugar daddy,
for want of a better term.

998
01:09:02,320 --> 01:09:06,108
He provided me with my drugs
whenever I rang up, you know.

999
01:09:06,200 --> 01:09:09,351
He was an importer
of crack cocaine and heroin.

1000
01:09:09,440 --> 01:09:13,433
Erm, it was like I hit gold
when I got him.

1001
01:09:13,520 --> 01:09:15,272
He ended up getting me married off.

1002
01:09:16,400 --> 01:09:21,155
Because he was a married man with
kids, he introduced me to a guy.

1003
01:09:22,560 --> 01:09:25,836
I fell in love with him
and ended up marrying him.

1004
01:09:25,920 --> 01:09:27,956
Half arranged, half love.

1005
01:09:29,600 --> 01:09:31,955
Well, I liked Saif instantly,
he was handsome.

1006
01:09:32,040 --> 01:09:35,476
You know, I am vain
and the first thing I do look at

1007
01:09:35,560 --> 01:09:37,915
is if somebody's handsome or not.

1008
01:09:39,880 --> 01:09:42,872
I had to spend nine week away
from Harris when I was in prison.

1009
01:09:42,960 --> 01:09:45,269
It was hell.

1010
01:09:45,360 --> 01:09:47,920
I missed his first birthday on a recall.

1011
01:09:49,120 --> 01:09:51,634
You know, I only ever got
one birthday with him.

1012
01:09:56,120 --> 01:09:59,590
And we think children
don't know what's going on.

1013
01:09:59,680 --> 01:10:03,673
I remember being in prison
and my husband bringing Harris up

1014
01:10:03,760 --> 01:10:05,910
and he was so angry.

1015
01:10:06,000 --> 01:10:10,630
Because not only had Mum gone, he
was now moved into a different house.

1016
01:10:10,720 --> 01:10:14,759
You know, fair enough he went
to my foster parents, to Ann and Steve,

1017
01:10:14,840 --> 01:10:18,594
he went to his nan and granddad,
but Mum wasn't there.

1018
01:10:18,680 --> 01:10:21,035
He wasn't waking up next to Mummy.

1019
01:10:23,480 --> 01:10:25,596
Some children,
you could give 'em to you

1020
01:10:25,680 --> 01:10:29,514
and they'd have screamed and carted on,
wouldn't they, you know what I mean?

1021
01:10:29,600 --> 01:10:31,556
At one year old... He weren't even one.

1022
01:10:31,640 --> 01:10:35,428
It were April so he weren't one
till June, so he were 11, ten month old.

1023
01:10:35,520 --> 01:10:37,875
Ten month old, that's a fact, yeah, ten.

1024
01:10:37,960 --> 01:10:40,554
He were as good as gold.
But what Lorraine did say,

1025
01:10:40,640 --> 01:10:43,029
"You've got to put six bottles
in his cot at night

1026
01:10:43,120 --> 01:10:45,509
cos if you don't,
he'll wonder what's going on."

1027
01:10:45,600 --> 01:10:47,909
And he'd drink 'em and sling 'em out,

1028
01:10:48,000 --> 01:10:50,594
drink 'em, sling 'em out,
till the morning.

1029
01:10:50,680 --> 01:10:54,639
And then, where the cot were there,
cot's there and our bed's there.

1030
01:10:54,720 --> 01:10:58,110
So we used to put... Cos he used
to stand up like that, looking at you.

1031
01:10:58,200 --> 01:11:00,953
As soon as you had eye contact
with him, that were it,

1032
01:11:01,040 --> 01:11:04,032
you had to either get up
or get up with him, be it whatever.

1033
01:11:04,120 --> 01:11:07,032
So we, we used to put, like,
a dressing gown round it.

1034
01:11:07,120 --> 01:11:10,510
And his head used to come up
and he'd be going...

1035
01:11:10,600 --> 01:11:11,874
He'd be looking for you.

1036
01:11:11,960 --> 01:11:14,838
And you'd laugh, cos I've got
a mirror and you could see him

1037
01:11:14,920 --> 01:11:17,992
and you'd laugh and then you'd think,
"Right, just get him."

1038
01:11:18,080 --> 01:11:20,355
So we'd put him
in the middle of us, bless him.

1039
01:11:20,440 --> 01:11:22,874
But he were not a minute's problem.

1040
01:11:22,960 --> 01:11:25,793
He smiled all the time.

1041
01:11:25,880 --> 01:11:28,235
He were absolutely gorgeous.

1042
01:11:33,040 --> 01:11:36,271
I think the job of a social worker
is so important.

1043
01:11:36,360 --> 01:11:40,319
Because we attended meetings,
where sort of we'd say summat

1044
01:11:40,400 --> 01:11:42,789
and then it'd be a revelation
to somebody else.

1045
01:11:42,880 --> 01:11:45,997
One of them didn't know
she'd had two children taken off her.

1046
01:11:46,080 --> 01:11:47,069
You know what I mean?

1047
01:11:47,160 --> 01:11:50,948
How could you make an informed decision
with so little knowledge?

1048
01:11:51,040 --> 01:11:54,919
They'd ask you on one hand
and disregard everything you'd said.

1049
01:11:55,000 --> 01:11:57,878
They promised us
a degree of confidentiality

1050
01:11:57,960 --> 01:12:02,829
but then went and told Lorraine, which
potentially caused a lot of conflict.

1051
01:12:02,920 --> 01:12:07,311
It got back to her. She said, "Why have
you been saying that about me?"

1052
01:12:07,400 --> 01:12:12,190
We suggested that it were more of
a weaning-off period back over to her.

1053
01:12:12,280 --> 01:12:15,078
Regular weight checks,
things like that.

1054
01:12:15,160 --> 01:12:16,275
He hadn't been eating.

1055
01:12:16,360 --> 01:12:19,591
She wrote a letter, "Don't you
accuse me of not feeding my son."

1056
01:12:19,680 --> 01:12:21,477
We didn't think she should have him.

1057
01:12:23,920 --> 01:12:27,833
Ann and Steve.
I put them through hell.

1058
01:12:27,920 --> 01:12:30,354
I knew they were looking after him.

1059
01:12:30,440 --> 01:12:33,318
You know, and I was
so grateful for them to do it,

1060
01:12:33,400 --> 01:12:37,996
but I was so jealous and envious
that he wasn't with me.

1061
01:12:38,080 --> 01:12:40,548
I wanted him with me,
where he belonged, with me.

1062
01:12:40,640 --> 01:12:44,155
I was just being
downright bloody selfish.

1063
01:12:46,040 --> 01:12:49,953
I just can't for the life of me see
how they could come to a conclusion,

1064
01:12:50,040 --> 01:12:54,636
that somebody heavily on drugs,
erm, with her background,

1065
01:12:54,720 --> 01:12:57,678
you know,
could think she were capable of,

1066
01:12:57,760 --> 01:13:02,276
you know, maintaining a normal,
safe environment for Harris.

1067
01:13:03,200 --> 01:13:07,512
You know, it just doesn't...
Doesn't sit right with me, anyway.

1068
01:13:07,600 --> 01:13:11,195
The only good thing to come out of that,
it were over a gradual thing.

1069
01:13:11,280 --> 01:13:13,714
She got him back over a few weeks.

1070
01:13:15,760 --> 01:13:18,274
I stayed on a methadone script.

1071
01:13:18,360 --> 01:13:22,353
I got off of it but I couldn't get
more than five days of abstinence.

1072
01:13:24,520 --> 01:13:27,273
I think I was having
a nervous breakdown.

1073
01:13:28,840 --> 01:13:30,990
I split up with my husband.

1074
01:13:31,080 --> 01:13:34,709
You know, I ended up
in a women's hostel.

1075
01:13:34,800 --> 01:13:37,155
My addiction got worse.

1076
01:13:43,960 --> 01:13:48,397
Two... Two...
Two years and one month.

1077
01:13:48,480 --> 01:13:52,837
He was talking, he was walking,
he'd feed himself, he was in a nursery.

1078
01:13:52,920 --> 01:13:54,512
He was a clever little boy.

1079
01:13:54,600 --> 01:13:57,034
I used to pick him up from the nursery
and he knew,

1080
01:13:57,120 --> 01:13:58,872
he'd run to me and go in my pockets

1081
01:13:58,960 --> 01:14:01,520
cos he knew I had sweets
in my pockets for him.

1082
01:14:02,400 --> 01:14:05,073
I said, "Why didn't you leave him
with me that night?"

1083
01:14:05,160 --> 01:14:07,037
If you knew you were looking for drugs

1084
01:14:07,120 --> 01:14:09,270
and you were going out,
why didn't you?

1085
01:14:09,360 --> 01:14:12,636
Because I'd lent her $20 that day
and I always think to myself,

1086
01:14:12,720 --> 01:14:14,950
if I hadn't had lent her the $20...

1087
01:14:15,040 --> 01:14:16,792
But it's like the policeman said,

1088
01:14:16,880 --> 01:14:20,111
"If it hadn't have been that day,
it would have been another day."

1089
01:14:20,200 --> 01:14:23,749
I'd got money off Ann
but then I couldn't score.

1090
01:14:23,840 --> 01:14:28,436
Erm, and I was
really, really withdrawing.

1091
01:14:29,520 --> 01:14:32,239
He was with me that morning but, erm,

1092
01:14:32,320 --> 01:14:35,153
I had stacks and stacks
of methadone in that cabinet.

1093
01:14:35,240 --> 01:14:37,708
Cos I used to use
and try not to take the methadone.

1094
01:14:37,800 --> 01:14:43,750
I used to take the methadone,
erm, when I really needed to.

1095
01:14:43,840 --> 01:14:48,550
But there was a certain drug dealer that
I used to sit down and smoke crack with

1096
01:14:48,640 --> 01:14:51,757
and, er, he just used to give me it.

1097
01:14:51,840 --> 01:14:53,751
But I couldn't get hold of him that day,

1098
01:14:53,840 --> 01:14:58,356
cos he, he hadn't, erm...
he hadn't got nothing on him.

1099
01:15:02,960 --> 01:15:05,474
He went to bed,
Harris went to sleep, obviously.

1100
01:15:05,560 --> 01:15:08,313
I think in the morning,
when she woke up, I don't know,

1101
01:15:08,400 --> 01:15:10,755
but you can presume,
she wanted to go to sleep,

1102
01:15:10,840 --> 01:15:12,592
he'd obviously wanted to get up.

1103
01:15:12,680 --> 01:15:15,797
Somebody'd heard her downstairs
shouting at Harris,

1104
01:15:15,880 --> 01:15:18,917
"Harris, get the eff to sleep."

1105
01:15:19,000 --> 01:15:23,039
They'd heard him running about because
the lady I went to the hospital with,

1106
01:15:23,120 --> 01:15:26,874
she said he'd got some nail varnish
and he'd been messing with it.

1107
01:15:31,320 --> 01:15:37,589
Erm, I went to sleep with him
on the bed. Yeah.

1108
01:15:37,680 --> 01:15:44,313
Erm, I had my hand and arm underneath
his head and we went to sleep.

1109
01:15:46,760 --> 01:15:49,354
I woke up and he never did.

1110
01:16:26,000 --> 01:16:29,675
I remember sitting
on a caravan step just crying,

1111
01:16:29,760 --> 01:16:35,596
just like, erm, what can you do?
You couldn't... In fact it hurts me now.

1112
01:16:36,800 --> 01:16:40,031
Well, there's nothing you can do
about it, you know what I mean?

1113
01:16:46,160 --> 01:16:47,957
Just awful.

1114
01:16:49,120 --> 01:16:51,759
A lot of people have got a lot...

1115
01:16:51,840 --> 01:16:55,992
It never... It can never be put right
because, erm...

1116
01:16:57,720 --> 01:17:02,874
...situations are as they are
and we'll have learnt lessons from this

1117
01:17:02,960 --> 01:17:06,509
but they won't learn lessons at all
cos...

1118
01:17:06,600 --> 01:17:10,309
Well, when she got him back,
obviously whatever circumstances,

1119
01:17:10,400 --> 01:17:14,109
whatever lifestyle she chose to live...

1120
01:17:18,200 --> 01:17:22,398
We've got to live with seeing
the cemetery every day, virtually,

1121
01:17:22,480 --> 01:17:26,917
you know what I mean?
How can it not occur to you?

1122
01:17:30,680 --> 01:17:32,989
Everybody let Harris down.

1123
01:17:33,080 --> 01:17:35,674
We didn't, with hindsight,
fight hard enough.

1124
01:17:35,760 --> 01:17:40,072
We made the right noises,
but they were pissing in the wind.

1125
01:18:18,120 --> 01:18:21,954
Lorraine came to see Kathy
after a few days,

1126
01:18:22,040 --> 01:18:24,793
but she looked like
she weren't bothered.

1127
01:18:24,880 --> 01:18:28,316
Kathy said, "Why ain't she crying?"

1128
01:18:28,400 --> 01:18:30,391
Cos if it had been her with her kids

1129
01:18:30,480 --> 01:18:33,756
and, like, I said,
if it were Nicole, if my child died,

1130
01:18:33,840 --> 01:18:36,673
I'd be in, I'd be in total meltdown.

1131
01:18:36,760 --> 01:18:40,070
I wouldn't be able to speak
to anybody for crying.

1132
01:18:40,160 --> 01:18:44,199
And she just walked in normal,
smiling and... It were weird.

1133
01:18:44,280 --> 01:18:46,316
It just all seemed weird
at that time.

1134
01:18:46,400 --> 01:18:51,428
But it's, like, I stuck up for her and
said, "People grieve in different ways."

1135
01:18:51,520 --> 01:18:55,877
And I even went to stay
with Lorraine for a night.

1136
01:18:55,960 --> 01:18:59,316
And, er, she asked me
if she could have Nicole for a week.

1137
01:18:59,400 --> 01:19:03,109
I said, "Can you hell." I said,
"You deal with losing your son."

1138
01:19:03,200 --> 01:19:05,998
Cos this were only
a couple of days after he died.

1139
01:19:06,080 --> 01:19:11,200
And she were wanting to have my child
and I was like, "No."

1140
01:19:11,280 --> 01:19:16,035
But... I don't know,
it's a horrible mess, that.

1141
01:19:22,320 --> 01:19:25,869
